class PyFSMwDB.FSM.FSM¶

Bases: object

A class that is used to create a finite-state machine(FSM) that can store states with code within it

run(inp=None, deadend_check: bool = True)¶

It will run the function, save its return value as ‘condition’ and ‘arguement’ if any, otherwise just ‘condition’. Condition will decide what module is run next and any argument will be passed to it. deadend_check will be passed down to any sub FSMs.

Parameters:

  • inp – input argument to be sent into the first function

  • deadend_check – whether a dead-end check will be run before execution

Returns:

whatever the last State returns

set_current_state(state: State)¶

Sets the input state as the starting point. By default, the first state added to the list will be the starting point.

Parameters:

state – the fsm will start from this state

Returns:

None

greater_than(inputV)¶

This function returns True if the greater than limit is less than the input value. The less than limit can NOT be set when using this function.

Parameters:

inputV – The value that will be compared to the value set during the set_greater_than operation

Returns:

True if self.__compareValueGreater is not None and self.__compareValueLess is None and self.__compareValueGreater < inputV else False

greater_than_limit(compare)¶

This function sets the upper limit for the greater than function

Parameters:

Compare – The value that the input value in the “greater_than” function will be compared to.

Returns:

self.__compareValueGreater

in_range(inputV)¶

This function returns True if the input value is between the upper and lower bound.

Parameters:

inputV – The value that will be compared to the values set during the set_in_range operation

Raises:

LogicException – The lower limit for in_range is larger or equal to the upper limit

Returns:

True if self.__compareValueGreater >= inputV and self.__compareValueLess <= inputV else False

in_range_limits(less, greater)¶

This function sets the lower and upper limit for a in range function

Parameters:

  • less – The lower value in the in range operation.

  • greater – The greater value in the in range operation.

Raises:

LogicException – The lower limit for in_range is larger or equal to the upper limit

Returns:

greater, less

less_than(inputV)¶

This function returns True if the less than limit is more than the input value. The more than limit can NOT be set when using this function.

Parameters:

inputV – The value that will be compared to the value set during the set_less_than operation

Returns:

True if self.__compareValueLess is not None and self.__compareValueGreater is None and self.__compareValueLess > inputV else False

less_than_limit(compare)¶

This function sets the lower limit for the lower than function

Parameters:

compare – The value that the input value in the “less_than” function will be compared to.

Returns:

self.__compareValueLess
